CatDescriptText: Cutline of image of Renetta Anderson, published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 21, 1956, pg. B14 reads: "Win Contest - These two young people won the annual Scholarship Contest sponsored by the Education committee of Deborah Grand Chapter, OES, in Schenley High School. Left, Miss Renetta Anderson of Steelton, won the oratory contest,...Both winners received a scholarship valued at $200. - "Teenie" Harris Photo."Cutline of image of Gail McNeal, published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 21, 1956, pg. B15 reads: "Runners-Up - ...Miss Gail McNeal of Huntington, center...were contenders in annual Scholarship Contest sponsored by Deborah Grand Chapter, OES, in Schenley High School.  They received $25 each for their efforts.  A total of $500 was awarded the young people.  Mrs. Iona Howard is state grand chairman of education. - "Teenie" Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of scholarship contest winners Gail McNeal and Renetta Anderson, posed in front of light colored wall in Schenley High School
